The paper deals with compressed sensing (CS) for wireless electrocardiogram (ECG) monitoring, which is a topic that falls under the information theory (cs.IT) and signal processing (cs.SI) sub-categories. The proposed method also incorporates prior knowledge about the wavelet representation of the ECG signal, which involves machine learning (cs.LG) and computer vision (cs.CV) techniques. Finally, the experimental results are obtained using the MIT-BIH Arrhythmia Database, which falls under the multimedia (cs.MM) sub-category.
